    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-12-16T22:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-12-16T22:15:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <head>290. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d290fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1960–63,
                            <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> 8 <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-12-16T22:15:00-05:00">December 16, 1963, 10:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2515. <gloss target="#t_SPC1">SPC</gloss>—Enlargement of Councils.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_SPC1">SPC</gloss> Dec 16 voted three reses: 15 seat <gloss
                            target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> (96–11–4), 27 seat <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1"
                            >ECOSOC</gloss> (95–11–4), and 25 seat Gen Comite. On <gloss
                            target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss>
                        negative votes were all from France, Sov bloc and Cuba. Albania voted in
                        favor. US, <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> (together with SAG and
                        Portugal) abstained on <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> and <gloss
                            target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> reses. China favored <gloss
                            target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> res but did not participate in vote on <gloss
                            target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss>, having alluded to Quaison-Sackey’s
                        (Ghana) reference to <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> seats of
                        “four permanent members of <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.” France
                        opposed both reses, explaining regret at <gloss target="#t_SPC1">SPC</gloss>
                        haste, referring to “problem of majority in <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                            >SC</gloss>,” and noting that it had expected abstain but had just
                        received instructions to oppose (suggesting a decision by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DGC1">De Gaulle</persName>).</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Wide agreement on <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> and <gloss
                            target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> reses developed after it became
                        apparent at <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss> group in morning that <gloss
                            target="#t_ASAF1">ASAF</gloss>s could not bring sufficient number <gloss
                            target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>s along with their reses to obtain two-thirds
                        majority. However, when <gloss target="#t_ASAF1">ASAF</gloss>s conceded to
                            <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>s one additional <gloss
                            target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> seat, 1 additional Gen Comite VP, and
                        commitment not to raid on <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss> seat in <gloss
                            target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> next year if enlargement reses not ratified,
                        entire <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss> group came along. <gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>s followed quickly obtaining one of additional
                        nine seats in <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> for themselves.
                        Final agreement expressed in form of <gloss target="#t_ASAF1">ASAF</gloss>
                        amendments to <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss> reses. Quaison-Sackey
                        explained that after ECOSOC increased by nine (7 <gloss target="#t_ASAF1"
                            >ASAF</gloss>s, 1 <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>, 1 <gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>) breakdown of 27 would be: 4 perms, 2 <gloss
                            target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>s, 4 <gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>s and
                        others, 5 <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>s, 12 <gloss target="#t_ASAF1"
                            >ASAF</gloss>s, of which 7 would be Africans, 5 Asians. In <gloss
                            target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> breakdown, 5 perms, 2 <gloss target="#t_LA1"
                            >LA</gloss>s, 1 <gloss target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>, 2 <gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss> and others, 5 <gloss target="#t_ASAF1"
                            >ASAF</gloss>s; there will be 3 Africans, 2 Asians, he said.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Gen Cmite res had separate vote on Polish-Czech amendment, as altered by
                        Nigerian wording which had one opponent, <persName corresp="#p_BB2"
                            >Bindzi</persName> (Cameroon) and eleven scattered abstentions. Pres
                            <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> and 17 VPs on 25 man Gen Comite now
                        will have following distribution: 7 <gloss target="#t_ASAF1">ASAF</gloss>s,
                        3 <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>s, 1 <gloss target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>s,
                        2 <gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>s and others, 5 perms, while Comite
                        chairmen will be 3 <gloss target="#t_ASAF1">ASAF</gloss>s, 1 <gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>, 1 <gloss target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>, 1
                            <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>, 1 alternating between <gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SAEII1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Stevenson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
